 at low temperatures below 20\\,K.\nInvestigating the slopes of spatial power spectra of dense gas tracer intensity\ndistributions (HCO$^+$, H$^{13}$CO$^+$, and N$_2$H$^+$), we find comparatively\nflat slopes between $-2.9$ and $-2.6$, consistent with high Mach numbers and/or\nactive star formation in DR20.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jul 2022 09:20:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
