gnetic field strength and length of the flare loops. In our\nwork, we used both single (about 60%), and double (about 40%) flare profiles to\nfit the observational data. The components of the double profile are supposed\nto be related to the direct heating of the photosphere by non-thermal electrons\nand back warming processes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Jul 2022 12:21:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-31"}
